1252
00:56:03,030 --> 00:56:04,690
But for the purposes
of this talk,

1253
00:56:04,690 --> 00:56:06,970
I'm going to concentrate
on this one right here,

1254
00:56:06,970 --> 00:56:11,700
which is based off of my PhD,
called Marine Cloud Brightening.

1255
00:56:11,700 --> 00:56:14,280
Now, marine cloud brightening,
the idea behind that

1256
00:56:14,280 --> 00:56:18,720
is, what if we could increase
the albedo or the reflectivity

1257
00:56:18,720 --> 00:56:19,930
of clouds?

1258
00:56:19,930 --> 00:56:22,200
And this could potentially
reflect sunlight back

1259
00:56:22,200 --> 00:56:25,398
into space as a
regional cooling.

1260
00:56:25,398 --> 00:56:26,440
Well, how does that work?

1261
00:56:26,440 --> 00:56:30,180
Well, so here, we
have a white cloud.

1262
00:56:30,180 --> 00:56:31,930
It reflects sunlight.

1263
00:56:31,930 --> 00:56:35,720
In contrast, a darker cloud
reflects less sunlight.

1264
00:56:35,720 --> 00:56:37,220
And the difference
between these two

1265
00:56:37,220 --> 00:56:40,620
is just the droplet size
within those clouds.

1266
00:56:40,620 --> 00:56:43,800
A white cloud is comprised
of smaller droplets,

1267
00:56:43,800 --> 00:56:47,510
whereas a rainy
cloud, the dark cloud

1268
00:56:47,510 --> 00:56:49,890
is comprised of large droplets.

1269
00:56:49,890 --> 00:56:52,880
And each of these droplets,
they grow on a seed.

1270
00:56:52,880 --> 00:56:57,213
And that seed is called a
cloud condensation nucleus.

1271
00:56:57,213 --> 00:56:58,880
The idea behind marine
cloud brightening

1272
00:56:58,880 --> 00:57:01,490
is-- what if we
could add more seeds

1273
00:57:01,490 --> 00:57:06,270
into existing clouds in the
form of sea salt crystals?

1274
00:57:06,270 --> 00:57:08,090
And we could do that
with a little ship

1275
00:57:08,090 --> 00:57:11,010
that sprays droplets
into an existing cloud?

1276
00:57:11,010 --> 00:57:14,180
And the idea is that
potentially, this

1277
00:57:14,180 --> 00:57:16,650
could brighten or
whiten the cloud,

1278
00:57:16,650 --> 00:57:21,150
increasing the solar
radiation reflection,

1279
00:57:21,150 --> 00:57:23,990
thus calling a local cooling.

1280
00:57:23,990 --> 00:57:26,660
And interestingly enough,
